are miscalculated, misinterpreted, hyped, or simply misleading. This new edition contains revised benchmark statistics, updated resources, and a new section on the rhetorical uses of statistics, complete with new problems to be spotted and new examples illustrating those problems. Joel Best’s best seller exposes questionable uses of statistics and guides the reader toward becoming a more critical, savvy consumer of news, information, and data. Entertaining, informative, and concise, Stat-Spotting takes a commonsense approach to understanding data and doesn't require advanced math or statistics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSocial problemsxStatistical methods. 0aSociologyxStatistical methods. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Demography.2bisacsh  aalarming statistics.  aanthropology.  acivic.  acrime.  acritical thinking.  ademography studies.  ademography.  adigesting statistics.  aeconomics.  aengaging.  afake news.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  ainteresting overview.  ajournalism.  alively.  amath and stats.  amathematics.  amedia criticism.  amedia.  apage turner.  apolitical.  apolitics.  apotential issues.  apropaganda.  areference.  aresearch stats.  aresearch.  arevised benchmark.  ascientific methods.  asocial problems.  asocial science.  asocial sciences.  asociology.  astatistical misuse.  astatistics.  aupdated resources.  aviolent deaths.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027998840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095707740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520957077423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520957077/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013